race.comment: Big field and plenty of pressure coming from out wide. ABOVE ME (9) just missed two back over 1000m then blew the start but got home hard when fifth at Donald latest. Looks suited here and should be winding up strongly. WINTER HAIL (8) led fresh when fourth then blew the start latest but still got home strongly to place this trip last time. Fitter again and should be doing best work late. PRINCESS PRUSSIA (18) wasn't the best away over a sharp dash on debut but did make good late ground. Spelled again and should be much improved. Worth keeping safe.  CAPITAL DESIGN (3) is a speedy galloper who has started twice and placed at each, both just over the border. Has a low draw and expected to take catching.
